Do not delete the original!

You forgot to DECRYPT the first time.

The solution is to make an image ( ImgTool Classic http://www.afterdawn.com/software/video_software/dvd_tools/imgtool_classic.cfm ) and then mount it with Daemon Tools or a similar program and open up with DVD Decrypter. 

DVD Decrypter will give a prompt when starting to make the image which says something like "strange this is encrypted when it should not be…do you wish to decrypt"

Choose "Yes to all".

When DVD Decrypter is done everything will be fine.
